{"title": "Red and the Black, Volume I", "description": "Stendhal - a German pen-name for a French writer who hated the English. Contemporary to some of the great names of French literature like Balzac and Flaubert, Stendhal is quite often considered a writer that doesn't seem to fit a defined genre. Some say he's a Romantic, others that he's a Modernist and that Le Rouge et Le Noir is the first modern novel. On one point they are all agreed: the novel is a masterpiece that shows a young theology student - Julien Sorel - intelligent, handsome and who is determined to rise above his humble peasant origins. Stendhal presents the reader with a satirical plot that will involve you in passions, intrigues, last-minute reversals and, mostly, the hypocrisy by which society operates. (Summary by sailormoon)", "duration": 33127, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "3042", "name": " Stendhal"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt24/red_black_1212.jpg", "copyright_year": "1830", "genres": ["General Fiction", "Suspense", "Espionage", "Political & Thrillers"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Sandra Luna"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Leni"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Gail Timmerman Vaughan"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "00 - Introduction", "readers": [6549], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_black_v1_1206_librivox/redandtheblack1_00_stendhal_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1402}, {"section": 1, "title": "01 - A Small Town", "readers": [3698], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_black_v1_1206_librivox/redandtheblack1_01_stendhal_64kb.mp3", "duration": 534}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - A Mayor", "readers": [3698], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_black_v1_1206_librivox/redandtheblack1_02_stendhal_64kb.mp3", "duration": 475}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - The Poor Fund", "readers": [6779], "path": "http://www.archive.org/down